          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-1" n="1">When Mother Clud had risen from play</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-2" n="2">And cald to take the Cards away</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-3" n="3">Van Saw, but Seem'd not to regard</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-4" n="4">How Miss pick'd every painted Card:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-5" n="5">And busy both with hand &amp; eye,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-6" n="6">Soon rear'd an house two Storyes high.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-7" n="7">Vans Genius without thought or lecture,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-8" n="8">Thus hugely turn'd to Architecture:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-9" n="9">Hee Saw y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Edifice &amp; Smil'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-10" n="10">Vow'd it was pretty for a chil'd:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-11" n="11">It was so perfect in its kind,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-12" n="12">Hee kept the model in his mind.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-13" n="13">But when he found the boys at play,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-14" n="14">And saw them dabling in their clay,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-15" n="15">Hee stood behind a Stall to lurk</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-16" n="16">And mark the progress of their work;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-17" n="17">With true delight observ'd them all</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-18" n="18">Raking up mud to build a wall;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-19" n="19">The plan he much admir'd &amp; took,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-20" n="20">The model in his Table-book:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-21" n="21">Thought himself now exactly Skilld</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-22" n="22">And so resolvd an house to buil'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-23" n="23">A real house with rooms &amp; Stairs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-24" n="24">Five times at least as big as theirs.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-25" n="25">Taller than Misses by two yards</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-26" n="26">Not a Sham-thing of clay or Cards,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-27" n="27">And so he did, for in a While</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-28" n="28">Hee built up such a monstrous pile,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-29" n="29">That no Chairman could be found</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-30" n="30">Able to lift it from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi>: ground.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-31" n="31">Still at Whitehall it Stands in View,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-32" n="32">Iust in y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Place where first it grew;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-33" n="33">There all y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> little school-boys run</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-34" n="34">Envying to See themselves outdone.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-35" n="35">From such deep rudiments as these</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-36" n="36">Van is become by due d,Egrees.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-37" n="37">For. building fam'd; &amp; justly reckon'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-38" n="38">At Court Vitruvius y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Second;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-39" n="39">No wonder since wise Authors Shew,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-40" n="40">The best foundations must be low:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-41" n="41">And now y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Duke has wisely ta'ne him,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-42" n="42">To be his Architect at Bleinheim.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-43" n="43">But raillery for once apart</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-44" n="44">If this rule holds in every Art:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-45" n="45">Or if his Grace was no more skill'd in</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-46" n="46">The Art of battering walls than building,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-47" n="47">Wee might expert to find next year,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-210L-line-48" n="48">A mouse-trapman Cheif Engineer.</l>
          </lg>
